It also mentions the recent movement for "algorithmic fairness" which is a topic often discussed in the machine learning community. Additionally, the paper uses Random Forest as a base learning algorithm which is a popular machine learning algorithm. 

The paper also involves image classification, which suggests it could belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Furthermore, the paper deals with interpretability of learning models, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). 

Finally, the paper involves deep neural networks, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
